13 Killed in Traffic Accident in Turkey
ANKARA , December 24 ( Xinhua ) -- Thirteen people were killed and at least 15 others injured Wednesday night when a passenger bus collided with a oil tanker in northern Turkey , the Anatolia News Agency reported Thursday morning .
The bus hit the tanker in Havza town of Samsun province near the Black Sea , setting the tanker aflame , the report said .
Fire-fighters rushed to the traffic scene and put out the tanker fire , said the agency .
The injured were taken to nearby hospitals for treatment .
An investigation into the cause of the accident is underway .
